<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from Cycle to Work Alliance (the Alliance) (CYS0044)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Written evidence from Cycle to Work Alliance (the Alliance) (CYS0044)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This submission is made by the Cycle to Work Alliance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (the Alliance)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, on behalf of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">its</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> members – Cyclescheme, Cycle Solutions, Evans Cycles and Halfords. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our comments are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> focussed on how the cycle to work sche</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">me can encourage people to take-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">up</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cycling,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">thus creating the critical mass to make </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the transport mode</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> safer. Additionally, we look at the role the scheme has in making vital safety equipment </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">more affordable for commu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ters who cycle to work. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The submission argues that better governmental promotion of the scheme could help increase up-take, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and improve the safety of cycling for Britons. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also consider the role employers can play in increasing the safety of their staff who commute </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to work by bike. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We recommend the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">committee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> calls on </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Government to ensure the scheme is adequately promoted, so as to increase the number of cyclists on the road</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and therefore improve their safety. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Introduction to the cycle to work scheme:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The cycle to work scheme is a government-supported, tax-efficient and salary-sacrificed employee benefit that provides a mode through which employers can encourage their worke</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rs to take up cycling.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Through the scheme, employers loan bicycles and safety equipment to their employees as a tax-exempt benefit for the purpose of commuting to and from work. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">At the end of the loan period, the employer may choose to give their employee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the option of purchasing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the bike and the equipment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The scheme can save employee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> up to 42% o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the cost of safety equipment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. By </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">doing so, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">scheme </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">incentivises riders to purchase the equipment that wil</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l make their cycle to work safer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To date, over 55</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">0,000 individuals have taken part in the scheme, which also involves over 2,220 bike retailers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> over</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">32</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,000 employers.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Although supportive of the scheme, Government could do more to aid its promotion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and remove barriers to entry</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">therefore delivering g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reater levels of sustainable transport and improving public health. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Encouraging cycling </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> changing behaviour</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">s</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A key element of the cycle to work scheme’s effectiveness in improving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cycling</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> safety is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> through</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increasing the critical mass of cyclists on the roads. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As CTC, the national cycling charity notes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> increasing cycling uptake is the surest way to improve safety. According to research, the Netherlands saw a 45% increase in cycling from 1980-2005 and a co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rresponding 58% decrease in cyclist fatalities</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Overall, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the CTC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> suggest that doubling the amount of cyclists on the road can reduce casualties by a third. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">With this in mind, the cycle to work scheme is a proven mechanism for increasing cycling uptake, a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nd therefore improving cycling safety.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> In the first half of 2013, industry data suggests </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">that the scheme encouraged over 44,000 commuters to start cycling to work by bicycle.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Research conducted by the Cycle to Work Alliance shows that 54% of scheme users </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">did not cycle to work up before they joined the initiative.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Similarly, 72% said they would not have bought their bike and safety equipment had they not been offered through the scheme.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The financial savings that commuters make on the cost of their bike an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">d the safety equipment through the scheme is the fundamental aspect in their decision to sign up to the scheme. 98% of scheme users say that the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">se savings were either important or very important in their decision to join the scheme, and start cycling to wo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rk. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Financial savings </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&amp; employer involvement</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Key to the positive impact that the cycle to work scheme has on cycling safety is the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">financial savings that scheme users make on the cost of safety equipment.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Through its tax efficiency, the scheme sees users</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> saving up to 42% on the cost of such equipment. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Similarly, a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ll members of the Cycle to Work Alliance have discussions with new users about the need for safety equipment, and the risks run if they chose not to wear such products. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Given the nature of the scheme as an employee benefit, it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">plays an important role in opening up the dialogue between employers and their staff on cycling and cycling safety. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusions &amp; recommendations</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The cycle to work scheme is a Government-back</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ed initiative that encourages people to commute to work by bike through making cycling and safety equipment more affordable.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">By doing so, the scheme increases the critical mass of cyclists on the road, which is arguably the most </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">effective way to improve th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e safety of cyclists. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Additionally, the scheme increases the affordability of cycling safety equipment, and all users are encouraged to invest this in this upon their initial interactions with providers of the cycle to work scheme. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Finally, the scheme is crucial in opening the dialogue between employers and employees on the merits of cycling, and related safety issues. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Alliance recommends that the Committee encourages Government to do more to promote the scheme, so as to improve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> cycling safety more generally. With the recent devolution of public health and sustainable transport responsibilities to local authorities, there is currently a concern that the scheme is not being adequately promoted. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">–</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Committee should call on Government – particularly the Department for Transport – to ensure that local authorities and employers are well aware of the scheme and its benefits to both users and improving cycling safety more generally. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> CTC</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">2007</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">Safety in Numbers </span><a href="http://www.ctc.org.uk/sites/default/files/ctc_safety_in_numbers_0.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.ctc.org.uk/sites/default/files/ctc_safety_in_numbers_0.pdf</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> Cycle to Work Alliance </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">2013</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">The Green Way to Work </span><a href="http://cycletoworkalliance.org.uk/news_41_2538974460.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://cycletoworkalliance.org.uk/n</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">ews_41_2538974460.pdf</span></a></p></body></html>